The paper deals with cognitive radio systems, which involve wireless communication and signal processing. The focus is on channel sensing and estimation, which are key components of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also considers the impact of sensing errors and fading channels on system performance, which falls under the category of control and optimization (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper specifically addresses cognitive radio channels, which are a subset of communication and information theory (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of pilot symbols for channel estimation, which is a common technique in multimedia systems (cs.MM).
